  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Global B2B2C Partnerships Lead",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Description</strong></p><p>Zuler is a global leader in remote desktop and cloud computing, revolutionizing connectivity with cutting-edge cloud rendering and real-time communication technologies. With over 180 million installed devices and a team of experts from top tech companies, Zuler delivers high-performance solutions that empower users worldwide.<br /><br /><strong>Role Summary</strong></p><p>This role builds DeskIn’s B2B2C distribution ecosystem by partnering with platforms, SaaS tools, agencies, schools, and communities that already serve large user bases. You will drive growth through bundles, integrations, affiliate programs, and joint go-to-market models.</p><p>Function: Community, Ecosystem, Growth</p><p>Location: Singapore</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Identify and close B2B2C partners: SaaS tools, PC brands, agencies, schools, platforms, communities</li><li>Build scalable collaboration models: (bundles, CPS/affiliate, reseller, co-content, co-launch)</li><li>Develop global partnership pipelines (US, JP, TW, SEA, EU)</li><li>Own partner lifecycle: prospecting → deal → launch → optimization</li><li>Work with Product & Growth teams on integrations and GTM strategy</li><li>Track partner performance and continuously improve ROI</li></ul><p><strong>Role Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>4–10 years in B2B, B2B2C, or ecosystem partnerships</li><li>Experience building distribution or channel partnerships</li><li>Strong commercial mindset and deal structuring ability</li><li>Background in SaaS, platforms, or tech ecosystems preferred</li><li>Ability to open new markets and build long-term alliances</li></ul>",
